symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.BulletChart
symbols.description: Chart that displays an actual value as a horizontal bar in semantic color on the top of the background bar, the numeric value, the scaling factor, along with the thresholds, and a target value as vertical bars.

deprecated.text: Deprecated. sap.suite.ui.microchart.BulletMicroChart should be used.

parameters.name: sId
parameters.description: id for the new control, generated automatically if no id is given

parameters.name: mSettings
parameters.description: initial settings for the new control

constructor.description:
Constructor for a new BulletChart. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. If the name of a setting is ambiguous (e.g. a property has the same name as an event), then the framework assumes property, aggregation, association, event in that order. To override this automatic resolution, one of the prefixes "aggregation:", "association:" or "event:" can be added to the name of the setting (such a prefixed name must be enclosed in single or double quotes). The supported settings are:
  • Properties
    • {@link #getSize size} : sap.suite.ui.commons.InfoTileSize (default: sap.suite.ui.commons.InfoTileSize.Auto)
    • {@link #getMode mode} : sap.suite.ui.commons.BulletChartMode (default: sap.suite.ui.commons.BulletChartMode.Actual)
    • {@link #getScale scale} : string
    • {@link #getForecastValue forecastValue} : float
    • {@link #getTargetValue targetValue} : float
    • {@link #getMinValue minValue} : float
    • {@link #getMaxValue maxValue} : float
    • {@link #getShowActualValue showActualValue} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowDeltaValue showDeltaValue} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getShowTargetValue showTargetValue} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowValueMarker showValueMarker} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getActualValueLabel actualValueLabel} : string
    • {@link #getDeltaValueLabel deltaValueLabel} : string
    • {@link #getTargetValueLabel targetValueLabel} : string
    • {@link #getWidth width} : string
    • {@link #getScaleColor scaleColor} : sap.suite.ui.commons.CommonBackground (default: sap.suite.ui.commons.CommonBackground.MediumLight)
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getActual actual} : sap.suite.ui.commons.BulletChartData
    • {@link #getThresholds thresholds} : sap.suite.ui.commons.BulletChartData[]
  • Associations
    • Events
      • {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.BulletChart#event:press press} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ChartContainer
symbols.description: Provides a toolbar with generic functions for tables and charts based on the VizFrame control like zoom, display in fullscreen mode, toggle the legend, switch between chart types, and changes of the chart dimension. The controls of the content aggregation are positioned below the toolbar. Additional functions can be added to the toolbar with the customIcons aggregation.

properties.name: showPersonalization
properties.description: Set to true to display the personalization icon. Set to false to hide it.

properties.name: showFullScreen
properties.description: Set to true to display the full screen icon. Set to false to hide it.

properties.name: fullScreen
properties.description: Display the chart and the toolbar in full screen or normal mode.

properties.name: showLegend
properties.description: Set to true to display the charts' legends. Set to false to hide them. See also showLegendButton.

properties.name: title
properties.description: String shown if there are no dimensions to display.

properties.name: selectorGroupLabel
properties.description: Custom Label for Selectors Group.

deprecated.text: Obsolete property as sap.m.Toolbar is replaced by sap.m.OverflowToolbar.

properties.name: autoAdjustHeight
properties.description: Determine whether to stretch the chart height to the maximum possible height of ChartContainer's parent container. As a prerequisite, the parent container needs to have a fixed value height or be able to determine height from its parent.

properties.name: showZoom
properties.description: Set to true to display zoom icons. Set to false to hide them.

properties.name: showLegendButton
properties.description: Set to true or false to display or hide a button for controlling the visbility of the chart's legend. Please be aware that setting this property to true indirectly is setting showLegend to false. If you need to hide the button but to show the legend, you need to set showLegend at a later point in time (onBeforeRendering). The execution order of the combined properties is not guaranteed by the control.

aggregations.name: dimensionSelectors
aggregations.description: Dimension Selects.

aggregations.name: content
aggregations.description:
ChartToolBar Content aggregation. Only vizFrame, sap.m.Table and sap.ui.table.Table can be embedded.
If not specified explicitly, the rendering order of the charts is determined by the sequence of contents provided by the application via this aggregation. That means, per default the first chart of the aggregation will be rendered within the container.

aggregations.name: toolBar
aggregations.description: Embedded ToolBar.

aggregations.name: customIcons
aggregations.description:
This aggregation contains the custom icons that should be displayed additionally on the toolbar.
It is not guaranteed that the same instance of the sap.ui.core.Icon control will be used within the toolbar,
but the toolbar will contain a sap.m.OverflowToolbarButton with an icon property equal to the src property
of the sap.ui.core.Icon provided in the aggregation.
If a press event is triggered by the icon displayed on the toolbar, then the press handler of
the original sap.ui.core.Icon control is used. The instance of the control, that has triggered the press event,
can be accessed using the "controlReference" parameter of the event object.

methods.name: getAutoAdjustHeight
methods.description: Getter for property autoAdjustHeight. Determine whether to stretch the chart height to the maximum possible height of ChartContainer's parent container. As a prerequisite, the parent container needs to have a fixed value height or be able to determine height from its parent. Default value is false

methods.name: getContent
methods.description:
Getter for aggregation content.
ChartToolBar Content aggregation. Only vizFrame, sap.m.Table and sap.ui.table.Table can be embedded. If not specified explicitly, the rendering order of the charts is determined by the sequence of contents provided by the application via this aggregation. That means, per default the first chart of the aggregation will be rendered within the container. Note: this is the default aggregation for ChartContainer.

methods.name: getCustomIcons
methods.description:
Getter for aggregation customIcons.
This aggregation contains the custom icons that should be displayed additionally on the toolbar. It is not guaranteed that the same instance of the sap.ui.core.Icon control will be used within the toolbar, but the toolbar will contain a sap.m.OverflowToolbarButton with an icon property equal to the src property of the sap.ui.core.Icon provided in the aggregation. If a press event is triggered by the icon displayed on the toolbar, then the press handler of the original sap.ui.core.Icon control is used. The instance of the control, that has triggered the press event, can be accessed using the "controlReference" parameter of the event object.

methods.name: getShowLegendButton
methods.description: Getter for property showLegendButton. Set to true or false to display or hide a button for controlling the visbility of the chart's legend. Please be aware that setting this property to true indirectly is setting showLegend to false. If you need to hide the button but to show the legend, you need to set showLegend at a later point in time (onBeforeRendering). The execution order of the combined properties is not guaranteed by the control. Default value is true

methods.description:
Set a date range that increments/decrements one calendar month at a time. The month date range begins on the first day of the month (beginning of the day) and ends on the
last day of the month (end of the day).

methods.name: setDateRangeWeek

parameters.name: dInitialDate
parameters.description: Any date that falls on the desired week. Start/end dates will be adjusted according to the first day of the week.

duration.name: duration
duration.description: The number of days in the range with a minimum of 1 and maximum of 7.

iFirstDayOfWeek.name: iFirstDayOfWeek
iFirstDayOfWeek.description: The starting day for the range. Valid values are 0-6, with 0=Sunday and 6=Saturday.

methods.description:
Set a date range that steps one week at a time. The starting date is set according to the first day of the week (default is Monday) and the initial date. For example, if the
first day of the week is set to Tuesday and the initial date is Wednesday, January 9, 2013, then the starting date will be Tuesday, January 8, 2013.

The last day of the range is calculated by adding (duration - 1) days to the starting date.

methods.name: setDateRangeYear

parameters.name: dInitialDate
parameters.description: Any date that falls within the desired year.

methods.description:
Set a date range that increments/decrements one calendar year at a time. The year date range begins on the first day of the year (beginning of the day) and ends on the last
day of the year (end of the day).

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.HeaderContainer
symbols.description: The container that provides a horizontal layout. It provides a horizontal scroll on the tablet and phone. On the desktop, it provides scroll left and scroll right buttons. This control supports keyboard navigation. You can use left and right arrow keys to navigate through the inner content. The Home key puts focus on the first control and the End key puts focus on the last control. Use Enter or Space to choose the control.

parameters.name: mArguments
parameters.description: the arguments to pass along with the event.

methods.description:
Fire event addCard to attached listeners. Expects following event parameters:
  • 'title' of type string The title of the note to be added.
  • 'body' of type string The text of the note to be added.
  • 'timestamp' of type object The timestamp of the note to be added.
  • 'viewAllTrigger' of type int The View All link appears in the Note Taker card when length of a body text exceeds the specified value.
  • 'thumbUp' of type boolean Indicates positive information for a new card.
  • 'thumbDown' of type boolean Indicates negative information for a new card.
  • 'attachmentFilename' of type string Stores the name of the file attached to the card.
  • 'uid' of type string The unique ID if available.
  • 'attachmentUrl' of type string Stores the URL of the file attached to the card.
  • 'card' of type sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard A newly created card if no data binding is available. If data binding is available, this parameter is empty.

parameters.description: initial settings for the new control

constructor.description:
Constructor for a new NoteTakerCard. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. If the name of a setting is ambiguous (e.g. a property has the same name as an event), then the framework assumes property, aggregation, association, event in that order. To override this automatic resolution, one of the prefixes "aggregation:", "association:" or "event:" can be added to the name of the setting (such a prefixed name must be enclosed in single or double quotes). The supported settings are:
  • Properties
    • {@link #getHeader header} : string
    • {@link #getBody body} : string
    • {@link #getTimestamp timestamp} : object (default: new Date())
    • {@link #getTags tags} : object (default: [])
    • {@link #getViewAllTrigger viewAllTrigger} : int (default: 1800)
    • {@link #getUid uid} : string
    • {@link #getIsFiltered isFiltered} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getThumbUp thumbUp} : boolean
    • {@link #getThumbDown thumbDown} : boolean
    • {@link #getAllTags allTags} : object (default: [])
    • {@link #getAttachmentFilename attachmentFilename} : string
    • {@link #getAttachmentUrl attachmentUrl} : string
  • Aggregations
    • Associations
      • Events
        • {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard#event:editNote editNote} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
        • {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard#event:deleteNote deleteNote} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
        • {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.NoteTakerCard#event:attachmentClick attachmentClick} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlow
symbols.description: Complex control that enables you to display documents or other items in their flow.

properties.name: foldedCorners
properties.description:
This property defines the folded corners for the single node control. The following values exist:
- true: means folded corner
- false/null/undefined: means normal corner

properties.name: scrollable
properties.description:
By default, the control body is embedded into a scroll container of fixed size, so the user
can put the control into a fixe sized layout.
When the control body (the graph) gets larger than the container cuts the overflowing parts of the graph and the cut parts can be viewed by scroling the control body.
When the control body fits into the container limits, obviously no scrolling is possible (and makes sense).

The scrolling feature can be turned off by setting this property value to false,
so the width/height of the whole control will change as the flow graph gets smaller/larger.
In this case the control body could not be scrolled, as the control body size matches the control container size.

properties.name: wheelZoomable
properties.description: The property specifies if to enable semantic zooming by mouse wheel events on desktop browsers.

properties.description: Defines if the connection labels are shown or not.

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowConnection
symbols.description: This control is used inside the ProcessFlow control to connect process flow node A with process flow node B in respect to the style(x) chosen by the application.

properties.name: drawData
properties.description:
This is an array of the following attributes for one element:
1. flowLine (string) - A connection definition where the line should be drawn. A string which defines a course of a flow line. A flow line is a connection between nodes in a process flow control. The string can contain the following characters:
- "r" for right,
- "t" for top,
- "l" for left,
- "b" for bottom.
2. targetNodeState (ProcessFlowNodeState) - A copy of the target node status. If the target node is created, the line is solid.
If the target node is planned, the line is dashed.
3. displayState (ProcessFlowDisplayState) - Display state of the node. This property defines if the node is displayed regularly, highlighted, or dimmed in combination with a selected visual style of the control.
4. hasArrow (boolean) - Indicates if the line has an arrow on the right end.

properties.name: zoomLevel
properties.description: This is a current zoom level for the connection. The point of connection to the node is derived from zoom level.

properties.description: Type of the connection.

deprecated.text: Type is deprecated because of no usages. There will be no replacement.

properties.description: State of the connection.

deprecated.text: State is deprecated because of no usages. There will be no replacement.

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowLaneHeader
symbols.description: This control gives you an overview of documents/items used in a process flow. The process flow is represented by the doughnut chart sections which are colored according to the documents status(es). This control can be used in two different ways. If you use it standalone, an event is fired and can be caught in to display the node map. If you use it with the node/document, it gives you an overview of the documents/items used in the process flow that is represented by the doughnut chart sections.

The user can explicitly set an array with the two properties state and value of the state, for example [state:sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNodeState.Neutral, value: 20]. Possible states are states are positive, negative, neutral, and planned.

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowLaneState
symbols.description:
This type is used in the ?state? property of the ProcessFlowLaneHeader. For example, as an app developer you have the option to set explicitly the status of the lane header outside of the control coding if the lanes are displayed without documents.
If the complete process flow is displayed (that is, if the lane header is displayed with documents underneath), the given state values of the lane header are ignored and will be calculated in the ProcessFlow according to the current state of the documents.

properties.name: state
properties.description: The ?state? property is associated with the given value. The possible states are: positive, negative, neutral, and planned.

properties.name: value
properties.description: In the ?state? array , the total sum of all values needs to be 100%.

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNode
symbols.description: This control enables you to see documents (or other items) in respect to their statuses  positive, negative, neutral, planned, planned negative. In addition to the node title (which can be optionally a hyperlink) also two other text fields are provided and can be filled. The process flow nodes consider all styles depending on the status they are in. The user can update or change the content of the node. The content of the node can be also filtered according to updated data and specific parameters set. This means that also the nodes style is affected.

properties.description: The node title.

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ProcessFlowNodeType
symbols.description:
Describes the type of a node. The type value could be single or aggregated. With this type,
the application can define if several nodes should be displayed as one aggregated node in a path per column to
represent a grouping of semantically equal nodes.

properties.description: Aggregated node - several nodes are illustrated as a stack of nodes in the same path and in one column.

properties.name: Single
properties.description: Single node - one node is illustrated in a column.

symbols.description: The zoom level defines level of details for the node and how much space the process flow requires.

properties.description: Zoom level for least details - only icon is displayed.

properties.name: One
properties.description: The full details with normal font size.

properties.name: Three
properties.description: The details are the icon, title text and no additional texts.

properties.name: Two
properties.description: The full detail view of the node but with smaller font size.

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.SplitButton
symbols.description:
The Split Button Control is a composite control that consists of a default-action Button and a Menu Button control.
The default-action button control represents a simple push button. It is used for initiating actions, such as save or print. It can contain some text, an icon, or both; the order of the two can be configured. The action initiated by this button is considered to be the default action for the control, and it must be one of the selections defined in the Menu Button menu.
The Menu Button control is a button that opens a menu upon user's click. MenuButton is a composition of the Menu control and the Button control and thus inheriting all features. When a menu item is selected by the user, MenuButton throws an event called itemSelected. The event transfers the itemId of the selected item. As an alternative, the button press event can be used which has a similar behavior.

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ThreePanelThingViewer
symbols.description: This control extends the sap.ui.ux3.ThingViewer control. The first panel can display a thing icon, a title, the Action Menu button, up to two rows of text descriptions (the first is wrapped, the second is truncated), vertical navigation bar (sap.suite.ui.commons.VerticalNavigationBar), and an image aka key visual. The second panel displays the header area as a vertical panel containing ThingGroup objects. The third panel is a main content area designed to display ThingGroup objects.

constructor.description:
Constructor for a new TimelineFilterListItem. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. If the name of a setting is ambiguous (e.g. a property has the same name as an event), then the framework assumes property, aggregation, association, event in that order. To override this automatic resolution, one of the prefixes "aggregation:", "association:" or "event:" can be added to the name of the setting (such a prefixed name must be enclosed in single or double quotes). The supported settings are:

    • {@link #getText text} : string
  • Aggregations
    • Associations

properties.name: maxCharacters
properties.description: The expand and collapse feature is set by default and uses 300 characters on mobile devices and 500 characters on desktops as limits. Based on these values, the text of the timeline utem is collapsed once text reaches these limits. In this case, only the specified number of characters is displayed. By clicking on the text link More, the entire text can be displayed. The text link Less collapses the text. The application is able to set the value to its needs.

events.name: navigate
events.description:
The event is fired when navigation between two pages has been triggered. The transition (if any) to the new page has not started yet.
This event can be aborted by the application with preventDefault(), which means that there will be no navigation.
This event is propogated from the inner NavContainer. The event can also return internal Master and Detail pages.

from.description: The page that was shown before the current navigation.

to.description: The page that will be shown after the current navigation.

toId.name: toId
toId.description: The ID of the page that will be shown after the current navigation.

firstTime.name: firstTime
firstTime.description: Whether the "to" page (more precisely: a control with the ID of the page that is currently navigated to) has not been shown/navigated to before.

isTo.name: isTo
isTo.description: Whether this is a forward navigation, triggered by "to()".

isBack.name: isBack
isBack.description: Whether this is a back navigation, triggered by "back()".

isBackToTop.name: isBackToTop
isBackToTop.description: Whether this is a navigation to the root page, triggered by "backToTop()".

isBackToPage.name: isBackToPage
isBackToPage.description: Whether this was a navigation to the root page, triggered by "backToTop()".

direction.name: direction
direction.description: How the navigation was triggered, possible values are: "to", "back", and "backToTop".

methods.name: fireAfterNavigate

parameters.name: mArguments
parameters.description: the arguments to pass along with the event.

methods.description:
Fire event afterNavigate to attached listeners. Expects following event parameters:
  • 'from' of type sap.ui.core.Control The page that had been shown before navigation.
  • 'fromId' of type string The ID of the page that had been shown before navigation.
  • 'to' of type sap.ui.core.Control The page that is now shown after navigation.
  • 'toId' of type string The ID of the page that is now shown after navigation.
  • 'firstTime' of type boolean Whether the "to" page (more precisely: a control with the ID of the page that has been navigated to) had not been shown/navigated to before.
  • 'isTo' of type boolean Whether was a forward navigation, triggered by "to()".
  • 'isBack' of type boolean Whether this was a back navigation, triggered by "back()".
  • 'isBackToTop' of type boolean Whether this was a navigation to the root page, triggered by "backToTop()".
  • 'isBackToPage' of type boolean Whether this was a navigation to the root page, triggered by "backToTop()".
  • 'direction' of type string How the navigation was triggered, possible values are: "to", "back", and "backToTop".

methods.name: fireNavigate

returnValue.description: whether to prevent the default action

parameters.name: mArguments
parameters.description: the arguments to pass along with the event.

methods.description:
Fire event navigate to attached listeners. Listeners may prevent the default action of this event using the preventDefault-method on the event object. Expects following event parameters:
  • 'from' of type sap.ui.core.Control The page that was shown before the current navigation.
  • 'fromId' of type string The ID of the page that was shown before the current navigation.
  • 'to' of type sap.ui.core.Control The page that will be shown after the current navigation.
  • 'toId' of type string The ID of the page that will be shown after the current navigation.
  • 'firstTime' of type boolean Whether the "to" page (more precisely: a control with the ID of the page that is currently navigated to) has not been shown/navigated to before.
  • 'isTo' of type boolean Whether this is a forward navigation, triggered by "to()".
  • 'isBack' of type boolean Whether this is a back navigation, triggered by "back()".
  • 'isBackToTop' of type boolean Whether this is a navigation to the root page, triggered by "backToTop()".
  • 'isBackToPage' of type boolean Whether this was a navigation to the root page, triggered by "backToTop()".
  • 'direction' of type string How the navigation was triggered, possible values are: "to", "back", and "backToTop".

constructor.description:
Constructor for a new VerticalNavigationBar. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. If the name of a setting is ambiguous (e.g. a property has the same name as an event), then the framework assumes property, aggregation, association, event in that order. To override this automatic resolution, one of the prefixes "aggregation:", "association:" or "event:" can be added to the name of the setting (such a prefixed name must be enclosed in single or double quotes). The supported settings are:
  • Properties
    • Aggregations
      • Associations
        • Events
          In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.ux3.NavigationBar#constructor sap.ui.ux3.NavigationBar} can be used as well.

symbols.name: sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater
symbols.description: This control extends the sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater control providing an ability to change data representation by switching between a number of views. The data can be displayed not only in rows but also in tiles that are adjusted to fill the entire horizontal space in a row.

deprecated.text: Deprecated. Standard Fiori technology should be used.

properties.name: itemMinWidth
properties.description: The minimal width of the tile for the current view. Only applicable if "responsive" property is set to true.

properties.name: responsive
properties.description: This parameter indicates whether the content is shown in rows or tiles. If false, the content is shown in rows just like in core sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater. If true, the content is shown in tiles (similar to sap.ui.ux3.DataSet control) that have minimal width defined by the "itemMinWidth" property. The number of columns depends on the parent control's width. If you resize the control, the number of columns may change respectively so that the content tiles can fill the entire space of a row.

properties.name: defaultViewIndex
properties.description: The index of the default view starting from 0. The view is selected on the initial rendering of the control. If the index is greater than the total quantity of the views, the last view is selected.

properties.name: showSearchField
properties.description: Indicates if the search field panel is shown.

properties.name: showViews
properties.description: Indicates if the view selector panel is shown.

properties.name: external
properties.description: Indicates if the external representation of the current view is rendered.

properties.name: itemHeight
properties.description: The height of the tile in the current view in pixels. Only applicable if the responsive property is set to true. This value is used for calculating the number of tile rows.

properties.name: height
properties.description: The height of the control. Only applicable if the responsive property is set to true.

aggregations.name: views
aggregations.description: The list of views for the data representation.

associations.name: externalRepresentation
associations.description: The control to be rendered instead of the repeater's own content.

events.description: This event is fired when the user performs a search.

newViewIndex.description: Contains an index of the new view in the Views aggregation.

filterId.description: Contains an ID of the filter in the Filters aggregation.

sorterId.description: Contains an ID of the sorter in the Sorters aggregation.

constructor.description:
Constructor for a new ViewRepeater. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. If the name of a setting is ambiguous (e.g. a property has the same name as an event), then the framework assumes property, aggregation, association, event in that order. To override this automatic resolution, one of the prefixes "aggregation:", "association:" or "event:" can be added to the name of the setting (such a prefixed name must be enclosed in single or double quotes). The supported settings are:
  • Properties
    • {@link #getItemMinWidth itemMinWidth} : int
    • {@link #getResponsive responsive} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getDefaultViewIndex defaultViewIndex} : int (default: 0)
    • {@link #getShowSearchField showSearchField} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getShowViews showViews} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getExternal external} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getItemHeight itemHeight} : int
    • {@link #getHeight height} : sap.ui.core.CSSSize (default: '100%')
  • Aggregations
    • {@link #getViews views} : sap.suite.ui.commons.RepeaterViewConfiguration[]
  • Associations
    • {@link #getExternalRepresentation externalRepresentation} : string | sap.ui.core.Control
  • Events
    • {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater#event:search search} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link sap.suite.ui.commons.ViewRepeater#event:changeView changeView} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater#constructor sap.ui.commons.RowRepeater} can be used as well.
